@startuml C4_Integrity_Backend

title C4 - Integrity Backend (facade and components)

top to bottom direction
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontStyle bold
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

package "shared/services" {
  class IpcGateway
  class IpcErrorHandlerService
  class TelemetryService
  class LiveAnnouncerService
}

package "integrity/facade" {
  class IntegrityFacade {
    +getState(): IntegrityState
    +isVerifying(): boolean
    +verifyDip(): void
    +verifyClass(classId: string): void
    +verifyProcess(processId: string): void
    +verifyDocument(documentId: string): void
    +reset(): void
  }
}

package "integrity/components" {
  class IntegrityPageComponent
  class IntegrityTriggerComponent
  class VerificationProgressComponent
  class IntegrityReportPanelComponent
  class IntegrityFailureDetailComponent
}

IntegrityFacade -down-> IpcGateway : invoke verify channels
IntegrityFacade -down-> IpcErrorHandlerService : map IPC errors
IntegrityFacade -down-> TelemetryService : track events and timings
IntegrityFacade -down-> LiveAnnouncerService : accessibility feedback

IntegrityPageComponent -down-> IntegrityFacade : request verify and read state
IntegrityPageComponent --> IntegrityTriggerComponent : trigger
IntegrityPageComponent --> VerificationProgressComponent : progress
IntegrityPageComponent --> IntegrityReportPanelComponent : report
IntegrityReportPanelComponent --> IntegrityFailureDetailComponent : failure detail

note right of IntegrityFacade
verify* methods are guarded by isVerifying.
If true, the request returns immediately.
end note

note bottom of IntegrityFacade
Verify channels are no-cache because checks mutate status.
Domain types and contracts are in C4_Integrity_Domain.
end note

@enduml
